\end{eqnarray}
evolving in the disk ${\cal D}_R=\{(r,\theta):r \in[0,R], \theta\in[0,2\pi)\}$, for $t>0$, with  boundary conditions 
\begin{eqnarray}\label{eqn-bcu}
u(t,R,\theta)&=&U(t,\theta),
\end{eqnarray}
where $U(t)$ is the actuation (we assume we can control all the boundary). Note that the system will be unstable for large values of $\lambda$.  

